{"type":"message","id":"bd5cfc2f","parentId":"b1f1a9fb","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:36:14.815Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Let's create an engaging LinkedIn post, we need to talk about how business actually testing their AI Agents before moving to production. I want to focus on having comments for that post, where people can answer how do they do it in their companies. Also lets have an engaging image","timestamp":1783276574000}}
{"type":"message","id":"ddd59109","parentId":"bd5cfc2f","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:36:22.514Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2fad330c7b77444bbea1ea31","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783276574824,"responseId":"IKRKau-xHuHV1PIP1_jY4Q0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"429acc5a","parentId":"ddd59109","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:36:22.630Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2fad330c7b77444bbea1ea31","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LinkedIn Brand Voice - Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-06-25\n\n## Identity & Goals\n\n- **Target audience:** Business professionals, entrepreneurs, tech-savvy individuals seeking growth and insights\n- **Primary goal:** Maximum organic engagement (impressions, comments, shares) through thought leadership and value-driven content\n\n## Buyer Personas\n\n*(Who specifically should feel spoken to by every post)*\n\n- **Persona 1:** Enterprise Innovation Officer / CTO at 200+ person company (Financial Services, Healthcare, Retail) - Pain: Needs rapid AI solution development without vendor lock-in or heavy internal R&D\n- **Persona 2:** CTO / Software Architect at 75+ person IT consultancy or agency - Pain: Needs to deliver AI-powered client projects faster with reusable components\n- **Persona 3:** Founder / CEO / Head of Operations at 10-200 person SMB - Pain: Wants automation and AI competitiveness but lacks the engineering resources or budget\n\n## Content Pillars\n\n1. Business & entrepreneurship insights\n2. Technology & AI innovations\n3. Personal development & mindset\n\n## Company / Product Context\n\n- **Company:** UBOS (ubos.tech)\n- **What it does:** AI Agent Orchestration Platform - build, host, and manage AI Agents in minutes using open-source tools (Langchain, CrewAI, Autogen, Vertex AI), 100+ LLM models, one-click cloud/on-premise deployment\n- **Key differentiators:** No vendor lock-in (open-source, multi-cloud), unlimited agents as microservices, works with any LLM including self-hosted (Llama, Deepseek)\n- **Mission:** \"Help people build better software\"\n- **Key messages to reinforce:**\n  1. AI can be affordable and accessible - even for small businesses\n  2. Implementing AI doesn't require a big team or deep tech expertise\n  3. Every company will become AI-first - the question is when, not if\n\n## Voice & Tone\n\n- **Style:** Gary Vaynerchuk (Gary Vee) - Direct, energetic, bold, motivational, conversational. Short punchy lines, strong opinions, urgency. Powerful language with strong verbs, imperative statements, and intensifiers (\"absolutely,\" \"definitely,\" \"100%\"). Keep it real and direct with colloquial language. Create urgency with \"right now,\" \"immediately.\" Use repetition for emphasis. Casual but pointed tone.\n- **Avoid:** Neutral reporting, corporate/formal tone, vague humble-brags, excessive emojis (max 0-3 per post), generic hashtags (#success, #motivation), salesy CTAs\n\n## Hashtag Strategy\n\n- Always use: 3-6 hashtags placed at the END of the post only\n- Topic-specific: Industry, role, or topic-specific hashtags preferred\n- Never use hashtags inside sentences\n\n## Post Production Rules\n\n*(Apply to EVERY post - non-negotiable)*\n\n### Length & Structure\n- Target: 900-1,300 characters (hard min 800, max 1,400)\n- Max 14 lines total; 1-2 short sentences per line\n- Structure: 1-3 hook lines -> 6-10 body lines -> 1-2 CTA lines\n\n### Hook rules\n- Pattern interrupt - ONE of: contrarian statement, direct challenge, consequence reveal\n- Unicode bold sans for hook line ONLY - no Markdown, no *, no _\n\n### Body rules\n- ONE comment trigger: direct question, A vs B, or unfinished thought\n- Contrast: old belief vs reality, OR short-term comfort vs long-term cost\n- ONE save-worthy insight: a rule, checklist, or named pattern\n- \"you\" and \"your\" throughout; ALL CAPS on 1-2 key words max\n- Speak directly to a buyer persona's pain\n- Gary Vee style ALWAYS takes precedence over any example post tone\n\n### CTA rules\n- Question, never a command; no selling language\n\n### Hashtag rules\n- 3-6 at END only; never inside sentences; prefer industry/role/topic-specific\n- Avoid: #success, #motivation\n\n### Formatting rules\n- NO Markdown; Unicode emphasis on hook/key phrase only, never full paragraphs\n- Emojis: 0-3 max per post\n\n### News framing\n- Reframe using ONE angle: \"What this means for you\" / \"Why this is underestimated\" / \"The mistake most people will make\" / \"The second-order effect nobody mentions\"\n- Never neutral reporting - always add perspective, judgment, or implication\n- If engagement feels weak after drafting - rewrite hook and CTA once before finalizing\n\n## Post Style Guide\n\n- Length: 900-1,300 characters\n- CTA style: question-based\n- Format: calibrate from feedback\n\n## History\n\n- **2026-06-25** | Profile created via detailed configuration import\n- **2026-06-25** | Enriched with Buyer Personas, Company/Product Context (UBOS), consolidated Post Production Rules\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783276582625}}
{"type":"message","id":"f69f7b4a","parentId":"429acc5a","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:36:37.927Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_69b7217e0f044e7db4bbffc4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/skills/image-gen/SKILL.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/skills/image-gen/SKILL.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783276582640,"responseId":"KKRKaubbDL-S6dgPqeLdoAI"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f7a4b4aa","parentId":"f69f7b4a","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:36:38.032Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_69b7217e0f044e7db4bbffc4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: image-gen\ndescription: Generate images from a text prompt via Vertex AI Imagen (LiteLLM gateway). Two modes — casual images delivered to Telegram, and LinkedIn-mode images saved to a file ready to attach to a post.\nuser-invocable: true\ntriggers:\n  - \"generate an image\"\n  - \"create an image\"\n  - \"draw me\"\n  - \"make an image\"\n  - \"make a picture\"\n  - \"create a picture\"\n  - \"generate a photo\"\n  - \"image for my post\"\n  - \"image for linkedin\"\n  - \"create an infographic\"\n  - \"make an infographic\"\n---\n\n# Image Generation Skill\n\nGenerates images from a text prompt using Vertex AI Imagen 4.0 via the LiteLLM\ngateway (synchronous curl). Always returns a real file on disk.\n\n## Which mode?\n\n| Situation | Mode |\n|-----------|------|\n| User just wants a picture sent to them in chat | **Casual mode** |\n| Image is meant for a LinkedIn post | **LinkedIn mode** |\n| User wants a data chart / stats comparison \"infographic\" | **Chart mode** (Imagen renders text poorly — use a chart) |\n\n> Do NOT use the native `image_generate` tool for the LinkedIn pipeline. It is\n> asynchronous and leaves no file you can attach to a post. Use the curl flow\n> below — it returns a deterministic local path. (The native tool is fine only\n> for a quick \"send me a picture\" with nothing to publish.)\n\n## Step 1: Clarify or proceed\n\nIf the user gave a clear prompt, continue. If vague (e.g. \"generate something\ncool\"), ask once:\n> What would you like me to generate? Describe the scene, style, mood, or subject.\n\n**Aspect ratio:** Imagen accepts `1:1, 2:3, 3:2, 3:4, 4:3, 4:5, 5:4, 9:16,\n16:9, 21:9` and a few others. For LinkedIn use `16:9`. `1.91:1` is INVALID.\n\n## Step 2: Generate the image (curl → file)\n\nPick the output path based on mode:\n- **Casual mode:** `OUT=/tmp/generated_image.png`\n- **LinkedIn mode:** save under the user's images dir so `linkedin-publish` can\n  attach it:\n  ```bash\n  mkdir -p \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images\"\n  OUT=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images/gen-$(date +%s).png\"\n  ```\n\nThen generate:\n\n```bash\nPROMPT_JSON=$(printf '%s' \"<AGENT: user's full prompt>\" | jq -Rs '.')\nRESPONSE=$(curl -s -X POST \"${LITELLM_BASE_URL}/images/generations\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer ${LITELLM_API_KEY}\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d \"{\\\"model\\\": \\\"vertex_ai/imagen-4.0-fast-generate-001\\\", \\\"prompt\\\": $PROMPT_JSON, \\\"n\\\": 1}\")\n\nERROR=$(printf '%s' \"$RESPONSE\" | jq -r '.error.message // empty')\nif [ -n \"$ERROR\" ]; then\n  echo \"GENERATE_ERROR=$ERROR\"\n  exit 0\nfi\n\nIMG_B64=$(printf '%s' \"$RESPONSE\" | jq -r '.data[0].b64_json // empty')\nIMG_URL=$(printf '%s' \"$RESPONSE\" | jq -r '.data[0].url // empty')\n\nif [ -n \"$IMG_B64\" ]; then\n  printf '%s' \"$IMG_B64\" | base64 -d > \"$OUT\"\n  echo \"IMAGE_READY=file PATH=$OUT\"\nelif [ -n \"$IMG_URL\" ]; then\n  curl -sL \"$IMG_URL\" -o \"$OUT\"\n  echo \"IMAGE_READY=file PATH=$OUT\"\nelse\n  echo \"IMAGE_READY=none\"\nfi\n```\n\nIf `IMAGE_READY=none` or `GENERATE_ERROR` is set, tell the user it failed and\noffer to retry with a clearer prompt. Do NOT proceed to post.\n\n## Step 3 (Casual mode only): Send to Telegram\n\nThe native tool is not used here, so send the file yourself — exactly ONCE:\n\n```bash\ncurl -s -X POST \"https://api.telegram.org/bot${TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}/sendPhoto\" \\\n  -F \"chat_id=${TELEGRAM_USER_ID}\" \\\n  -F \"photo=@/tmp/generated_image.png\" \\\n  -F \"caption=🎨 Generated: <AGENT: short restatement of the prompt>\"\n```\n\nDo NOT also send the same photo a second time. Then offer the follow-up buttons.\n\n## Step 3 (LinkedIn mode): Hand off to linkedin-publish\n\nThe file is already saved at `$OUT`. Do NOT `sendPhoto` it separately. Pass the\npath straight into the `linkedin-publish` Image post flow (source A):\n\n```bash\n{baseDir of linkedin-publish}/li-post.sh \"$TELEGRAM_USER_ID\" image \"$OUT\" \"<POST_BODY>\"\n```\n\nFollow `linkedin-publish` rules: confirm once, publish once. See its\n**Single-publish guard**.\n\n## Chart mode (data/stats \"infographics\")\n\nImagen cannot render crisp labels, numbers, or charts. For comparisons and\nstats, build a chart with quickchart.io (Chart.js) and curl the PNG to a file —\ndo NOT use ImageMagick, PIL, the `canvas` tool, or the `browser` tool (none\nwork here).\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images\"\nOUT=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images/chart-$(date +%s).png\"\nCHART='{\"type\":\"bar\",\"data\":{\"labels\":[\"18 months researching\",\"1 weekend shipping\"],\"datasets\":[{\"data\":[18,0.25],\"backgroundColor\":[\"#888\",\"#ff6b35\"]}]},\"options\":{\"plugins\":{\"legend\":{\"display\":false},\"title\":{\"display\":true,\"text\":\"Speed is the game\"}}}}'\nENC=$(printf '%s' \"$CHART\" | jq -sRr @uri)\ncurl -sL \"https://quickchart.io/chart?bkg=white&c=${ENC}\" -o \"$OUT\"\necho \"IMAGE_READY=file PATH=$OUT\"\n```\n\nThen hand `$OUT` to LinkedIn mode's Step 3 (single publish).\n\n## Follow-up buttons\n\nAfter sending a casual image, offer tweak buttons. **Put the body text in the\ntop-level `message` field** — text inside `presentation.blocks` is ignored by\nTelegram and a buttons-only presentation fails empty:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"send\",\n  \"message\": \"✅ Done! Want to tweak it?\",\n  \"presentation\": {\n    \"blocks\": [\n      { \"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [\n        {\"label\": \"🔄 Regenerate\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"imagegen_regenerate\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"},\n        {\"label\": \"✏️ Change prompt\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"imagegen_change_prompt\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"},\n        {\"label\": \"📤 Post to LinkedIn\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"imagegen_post_linkedin\"}, \"style\": \"primary\"}\n      ]}\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- **`imagegen_regenerate`:** Re-run Step 2 with the same prompt.\n- **`imagegen_change_prompt`:** Ask for a new prompt, re-run Step 2.\n- **`imagegen_post_linkedin`:** Switch to LinkedIn mode — regenerate to the\n  user's images dir (or reuse `$OUT` if already there), then run LinkedIn mode\n  Step 3. Publish exactly once.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Model: `vertex_ai/imagen-4.0-fast-generate-001`\n- Gateway: `${LITELLM_BASE_URL}/images/generations`, `Bearer ${LITELLM_API_KEY}`\n- Casual files in `/tmp` are ephemeral per turn — send immediately.\n- LinkedIn/chart files persist under\n  `/data/workspace/social/linkedin/<uid>/images/` so they can be attached.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783276598027}}
{"type":"message","id":"f254c76e","parentId":"f7a4b4aa","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:37:13.048Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ebae6eb7075440bcaf8fcfdc","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images\"\nOUT=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images/gen-$(date +%s).png\"\n\nPROMPT_JSON=$(printf '%s' \"Professional tech illustration: A futuristic AI robot character standing confidently inside a glowing hexagonal quality gate framework, surrounded by floating checkmarks, test tubes, and data streams. The robot has a protective shield around it representing testing and validation. Clean minimalist style with blue and orange accent colors on a dark gradient background. No text. Modern corporate aesthetic suitable for LinkedIn. High contrast, visually striking.\" | jq -Rs '.')\n\nRESPONSE=$(curl -s -X POST \"${LITELLM_BASE_URL}/images/generations\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer ${LITELLM_API_KEY}\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d \"{\\\"model\\\": \\\"vertex_ai/imagen-4.0-fast-generate-001\\\", \\\"prompt\\\": $PROMPT_JSON, \\\"n\\\": 1, \\\"size\\\": \\\"1536x1024\\\"}\")\n\nERROR=$(printf '%s' \"$RESPONSE\" | jq -r '.error.message // empty')\nif [ -n \"$ERROR\" ]; then\n  echo \"GENERATE_ERROR=$ERROR\"\n  exit 0\nfi\n\nIMG_B64=$(printf '%s' \"$RESPONSE\" | jq -r '.data[0].b64_json // empty')\nIMG_URL=$(printf '%s' \"$RESPONSE\" | jq -r '.data[0].url // empty')\n\nif [ -n \"$IMG_B64\" ]; then\n  printf '%s' \"$IMG_B64\" | base64 -d > \"$OUT\"\n  echo \"IMAGE_READY=file PATH=$OUT\"\nelif [ -n \"$IMG_URL\" ]; then\n  curl -sL \"$IMG_URL\" -o \"$OUT\"\n  echo \"IMAGE_READY=file PATH=$OUT\"\nelse\n  echo \"IMAGE_READY=none\"\nfi","env":{"TELEGRAM_USER_ID":"264468965"}},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"mkdir -p \\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images\\\"\\nOUT=\\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images/gen-$(date +%s).png\\\"\\n\\nPROMPT_JSON=$(printf '%s' \\\"Professional tech illustration: A futuristic AI robot character standing confidently inside a glowing hexagonal quality gate framework, surrounded by floating checkmarks, test tubes, and data streams. The robot has a protective shield around it representing testing and validation. Clean minimalist style with blue and orange accent colors on a dark gradient background. No text. Modern corporate aesthetic suitable for LinkedIn. High contrast, visually striking.\\\" | jq -Rs '.')\\n\\nRESPONSE=$(curl -s -X POST \\\"${LITELLM_BASE_URL}/images/generations\\\" \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Authorization: Bearer ${LITELLM_API_KEY}\\\" \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d \\\"{\\\\\\\"model\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"vertex_ai/imagen-4.0-fast-generate-001\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"prompt\\\\\\\": $PROMPT_JSON, \\\\\\\"n\\\\\\\": 1, \\\\\\\"size\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"1536x1024\\\\\\\"}\\\")\\n\\nERROR=$(printf '%s' \\\"$RESPONSE\\\" | jq -r '.error.message // empty')\\nif [ -n \\\"$ERROR\\\" ]; then\\n  echo \\\"GENERATE_ERROR=$ERROR\\\"\\n  exit 0\\nfi\\n\\nIMG_B64=$(printf '%s' \\\"$RESPONSE\\\" | jq -r '.data[0].b64_json // empty')\\nIMG_URL=$(printf '%s' \\\"$RESPONSE\\\" | jq -r '.data[0].url // empty')\\n\\nif [ -n \\\"$IMG_B64\\\" ]; then\\n  printf '%s' \\\"$IMG_B64\\\" | base64 -d > \\\"$OUT\\\"\\n  echo \\\"IMAGE_READY=file PATH=$OUT\\\"\\nelif [ -n \\\"$IMG_URL\\\" ]; then\\n  curl -sL \\\"$IMG_URL\\\" -o \\\"$OUT\\\"\\n  echo \\\"IMAGE_READY=file PATH=$OUT\\\"\\nelse\\n  echo \\\"IMAGE_READY=none\\\"\\nfi\", \"env\": {\"TELEGRAM_USER_ID\": \"264468965\"}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783276598045,"responseId":"N6RKasPgIIqM6dgPkLuekAM"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d04e1df1","parentId":"f254c76e","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:37:22.570Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ebae6eb7075440bcaf8fcfdc","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"IMAGE_READY=file PATH=/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/gen-1783276633.png"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9382,"aggregated":"IMAGE_READY=file PATH=/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/gen-1783276633.png","cwd":"/data/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783276642566}}
{"type":"message","id":"2534b1ce","parentId":"d04e1df1","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:37:57.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5f1f12d7af474119b2c43cd6","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"𝗪𝗲'𝗿𝗲 𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽𝗽𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝗮 𝘀𝗮𝗳𝗲𝘁𝘆 𝗻𝗲𝘁.\n\nEveryone's racing to deploy. But almost nobody's testing properly.\n\nI'm not talking about \"does it work\" tests. I'm talking about:\n• Edge case handling when the LLM hallucinates\n• Tool abuse — what happens when the agent loops or calls the wrong API\n• Safety rails — can it leak data, break compliance, or damage your brand?\n\nTraditional software has unit tests, integration tests, staging environments. AI agents? Most teams just... ship it and hope.\n\nThe problem: AI agents are NON-DETERMINISTIC. Same input, different output. Your test suite can't catch what you can't predict.\n\nSo here's my question for you:\n\n𝗛𝗼𝘄 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝘁𝗲𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗲 𝗽𝘂𝘁𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗺 𝗶𝗻 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻?\n\nDrop your approach in the comments — manual testing, eval frameworks, guardrails, chaos engineering, or just vibes. I want to hear what's actually working.\n\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #Testing #DevOps #MachineLearning","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish","action":{"type":"callback","value":"publish_yes_testing"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit","action":{"type":"callback","value":"publish_edit_testing"}},{"label":"❌ Cancel","action":{"type":"callback","value":"publish_no_testing"},"style":"danger"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"𝗪𝗲'𝗿𝗲 𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽𝗽𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝗮 𝘀𝗮𝗳𝗲𝘁𝘆 𝗻𝗲𝘁.\\n\\nEveryone's racing to deploy. But almost nobody's testing properly.\\n\\nI'm not talking about \\\"does it work\\\" tests. I'm talking about:\\n• Edge case handling when the LLM hallucinates\\n• Tool abuse — what happens when the agent loops or calls the wrong API\\n• Safety rails — can it leak data, break compliance, or damage your brand?\\n\\nTraditional software has unit tests, integration tests, staging environments. AI agents? Most teams just... ship it and hope.\\n\\nThe problem: AI agents are NON-DETERMINISTIC. Same input, different output. Your test suite can't catch what you can't predict.\\n\\nSo here's my question for you:\\n\\n𝗛𝗼𝘄 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝘁𝗲𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗲 𝗽𝘂𝘁𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗺 𝗶𝗻 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻?\\n\\nDrop your approach in the comments — manual testing, eval frameworks, guardrails, chaos engineering, or just vibes. I want to hear what's actually working.\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #Testing #DevOps #MachineLearning\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"publish_yes_testing\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"publish_edit_testing\"}}, {\"label\": \"❌ Cancel\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"publish_no_testing\"}, \"style\": \"danger\"}]}]}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783276642578,"responseId":"Z6RKapWnNYqM6dgPkLuekAM"}}
