{"type":"message","id":"363cbdb3","parentId":"5f198e83","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:38:59.083Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_489ea7117c5146faa7e2650f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh \"264468965\" image \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/gen-1783276633.png\" \"We're shipping AI agents without a safety net.\n\nEveryone's racing to deploy. But almost nobody's testing properly.\n\nI'm not talking about \\\"does it work\\\" tests. I'm talking about:\n• Edge case handling when the LLM hallucinates\n• Tool abuse — what happens when the agent loops or calls the wrong API\n• Safety rails — can it leak data, break compliance, or damage your brand?\n\nTraditional software has unit tests, integration tests, staging environments. AI agents? Most teams just... ship it and hope.\n\nThe problem: AI agents are NON-DETERMINISTIC. Same input, different output. Your test suite can't catch what you can't predict.\n\nSo here's my question for you:\n\nHow are you testing your AI agents before putting them in production?\n\nDrop your approach in the comments — manual testing, eval frameworks, guardrails, chaos engineering, or just vibes. I want to hear what's actually working.\n\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #Testing #DevOps #MachineLearning\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh \\\"264468965\\\" image \\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/gen-1783276633.png\\\" \\\"We're shipping AI agents without a safety net.\\n\\nEveryone's racing to deploy. But almost nobody's testing properly.\\n\\nI'm not talking about \\\\\\\"does it work\\\\\\\" tests. I'm talking about:\\n• Edge case handling when the LLM hallucinates\\n• Tool abuse — what happens when the agent loops or calls the wrong API\\n• Safety rails — can it leak data, break compliance, or damage your brand?\\n\\nTraditional software has unit tests, integration tests, staging environments. AI agents? Most teams just... ship it and hope.\\n\\nThe problem: AI agents are NON-DETERMINISTIC. Same input, different output. Your test suite can't catch what you can't predict.\\n\\nSo here's my question for you:\\n\\nHow are you testing your AI agents before putting them in production?\\n\\nDrop your approach in the comments — manual testing, eval frameworks, guardrails, chaos engineering, or just vibes. I want to hear what's actually working.\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #Testing #DevOps #MachineLearning\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783276730514,"responseId":"vKRKaoHNA-HV1PIP1_jY4Q0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5f537164","parentId":"363cbdb3","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:39:01.610Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_489ea7117c5146faa7e2650f","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7479604768227876865/\nDISPLAY_NAME: Andrii Bidochko\nCHARS: 970"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2371,"aggregated":"OK: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7479604768227876865/\nDISPLAY_NAME: Andrii Bidochko\nCHARS: 970","cwd":"/data/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783276741608}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f7f01d0","parentId":"5f537164","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:39:07.500Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ Published to LinkedIn (as Andrii Bidochko):\n→ https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7479604768227876865/\n\nCharacters: 970"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_388855ee818f46fabbe20982","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-05-were-shipping-ai-agents-without-a.md","content":"# We're shipping AI agents without a safety net\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-05T18:38:55Z\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7479604768227876865/\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7479604768227876865\n**Format:** image\n**Characters:** 970\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/gen-1783276633.png\n\n## Post Body\n\nWe're shipping AI agents without a safety net.\n\nEveryone's racing to deploy. But almost nobody's testing properly.\n\nI'm not talking about \"does it work\" tests. I'm talking about:\n• Edge case handling when the LLM hallucinates\n• Tool abuse — what happens when the agent loops or calls the wrong API\n• Safety rails — can it leak data, break compliance, or damage your brand?\n\nTraditional software has unit tests, integration tests, staging environments. AI agents? Most teams just... ship it and hope.\n\nThe problem: AI agents are NON-DETERMINISTIC. Same input, different output. Your test suite can't catch what you can't predict.\n\nSo here's my question for you:\n\nHow are you testing your AI agents before putting them in production?\n\nDrop your approach in the comments — manual testing, eval frameworks, guardrails, chaos engineering, or just vibes. I want to hear what's actually working.\n\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #Testing #DevOps #MachineLearning\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-05-were-shipping-ai-agents-without-a.md\", \"content\": \"# We're shipping AI agents without a safety net\\n\\n**Published:** 2026-07-05T18:38:55Z\\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7479604768227876865/\\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7479604768227876865\\n**Format:** image\\n**Characters:** 970\\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/gen-1783276633.png\\n\\n## Post Body\\n\\nWe're shipping AI agents without a safety net.\\n\\nEveryone's racing to deploy. But almost nobody's testing properly.\\n\\nI'm not talking about \\\"does it work\\\" tests. I'm talking about:\\n• Edge case handling when the LLM hallucinates\\n• Tool abuse — what happens when the agent loops or calls the wrong API\\n• Safety rails — can it leak data, break compliance, or damage your brand?\\n\\nTraditional software has unit tests, integration tests, staging environments. AI agents? Most teams just... ship it and hope.\\n\\nThe problem: AI agents are NON-DETERMINISTIC. Same input, different output. Your test suite can't catch what you can't predict.\\n\\nSo here's my question for you:\\n\\nHow are you testing your AI agents before putting them in production?\\n\\nDrop your approach in the comments — manual testing, eval frameworks, guardrails, chaos engineering, or just vibes. I want to hear what's actually working.\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #Testing #DevOps #MachineLearning\\n\\n## Performance\\n\\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\\n\\n- **Impressions:** —\\n- **Reactions:** —\\n- **Comments:** —\\n- **Shares:** —\\n- **Last checked:** —\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783276741625,"responseId":"xqRKapT1Jv6B_NUPxo2uoQY"}}
