{"type":"message","id":"10fa60bf","parentId":"a417ba76","timestamp":"2026-07-06T00:44:35.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Web search unavailable — I'll draft evergreen posts from your pillars instead of fresh news. Let me create 2-3 publish-ready posts."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9daa247cedfe4ab984e76a53","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"UID=\"264468965\"\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nPENDING_DIR=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending\"\nmkdir -p \"$PENDING_DIR\"\n\n# Draft 1 - Business & entrepreneurship\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-1.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-06\nn: 1\npillar: Business & entrepreneurship insights\nsource: evergreen\nsource_date: 2026-07-06\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗳𝗶𝗿𝘀𝘁 𝟭𝟬 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝘄𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗲 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗸𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴.\n\nThey'll come from conversations.\n\nThe startup myth: build it, launch it, run ads, scale. The reality? Most early customers come from direct outreach, founder-led sales, and word-of-mouth from people who actually know you.\n\nMarketing kicks in LATER — once you have signal on what resonates, who buys, and why they stay.\n\nBefore that? You're not a marketer. You're a salesperson with a prototype.\n\nThe founders who win early don't optimize funnels. They send 50 DMs a day, get on calls, listen to objections, and iterate. They build relationships with 10 people who become their first champions.\n\nThose 10 turn into 100. Then marketing scales it.\n\nBut you can't skip the unscalable part.\n\nWhat's one unscalable thing you're doing this week to get your next 10 customers?\n\n#Entrepreneurship #Startups #Sales #Growth #BusinessStrategy\nDRAFT_EOF\n\n# Draft 2 - Technology & AI innovations\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-2.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-06\nn: 2\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: evergreen\nsource_date: 2026-07-06\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗱𝗿𝘂𝗱𝗴𝗲𝗿𝘆. 𝗕𝘂𝘁 𝘄𝗵𝗼'𝘀 𝘄𝗮𝘁𝗰𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗺?\n\nEvery company is now an \"AI company.\" Agents handling support, writing code, qualifying leads, running workflows.\n\nHere's what nobody talks about:\n\nAn AI agent is like hiring an intern who works 24/7, never complains, but also never tells you when they're about to make a catastrophic mistake.\n\nNo performance review. No guardrails. Just... output.\n\nThe companies that win with AI aren't the ones deploying the most agents. They're the ones who:\n• Define clear boundaries for what agents CAN'T do\n• Build observability so humans see when things go weird\n• Test edge cases before customers find them\n• Keep humans in the loop for high-stakes decisions\n\nAI doesn't replace judgment. It amplifies whatever you point it at — good or bad.\n\nWhat's the last thing you automated that maybe you shouldn't have?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Automation #TechLeadership #FutureOfWork\nDRAFT_EOF\n\n# Draft 3 - Personal development & mindset\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-3.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-06\nn: 3\npillar: Personal development & mindset\nsource: evergreen\nsource_date: 2026-07-06\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗴𝗮𝗽 𝗯𝗲𝘁𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗻 𝘄𝗵𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝘄𝗵𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝘄𝗮𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗯𝗲 𝗶𝘀 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗮 𝗹𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗼𝗳 𝗸𝗻𝗼𝘄𝗹𝗲𝗱𝗴𝗲.\n\nIt's a lack of reps.\n\nWe consume content, read books, take courses, follow thought leaders. We KNOW what to do. But knowing isn't doing.\n\nThe difference between the top 1% and everyone else isn't access to information — it's the willingness to be bad at something in public until you're not.\n\n• The writer who publishes daily even when nobody reads\n• The founder who pitches 100 investors to get 1 yes\n• The engineer who ships messy code and refactors later\n\nEvery expert was once a beginner who refused to quit.\n\nThe reps are free. The discomfort is the price.\n\nWhat are you putting off because you're \"not ready yet\"?\n\n#PersonalDevelopment #Growth #Mindset #Habits #Success\nDRAFT_EOF\n\n# Mark brief as sent\ntouch \"$PENDING_DIR/.brief-sent-$TODAY\"\n\necho \"DRAFTS_CREATED=3\"\nls -la \"$PENDING_DIR/\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"UID=\\\"264468965\\\"\\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\\nPENDING_DIR=\\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending\\\"\\nmkdir -p \\\"$PENDING_DIR\\\"\\n\\n# Draft 1 - Business & entrepreneurship\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-1.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-06\\nn: 1\\npillar: Business & entrepreneurship insights\\nsource: evergreen\\nsource_date: 2026-07-06\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗳𝗶𝗿𝘀𝘁 𝟭𝟬 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝘄𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗲 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗸𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴.\\n\\nThey'll come from conversations.\\n\\nThe startup myth: build it, launch it, run ads, scale. The reality? Most early customers come from direct outreach, founder-led sales, and word-of-mouth from people who actually know you.\\n\\nMarketing kicks in LATER — once you have signal on what resonates, who buys, and why they stay.\\n\\nBefore that? You're not a marketer. You're a salesperson with a prototype.\\n\\nThe founders who win early don't optimize funnels. They send 50 DMs a day, get on calls, listen to objections, and iterate. They build relationships with 10 people who become their first champions.\\n\\nThose 10 turn into 100. Then marketing scales it.\\n\\nBut you can't skip the unscalable part.\\n\\nWhat's one unscalable thing you're doing this week to get your next 10 customers?\\n\\n#Entrepreneurship #Startups #Sales #Growth #BusinessStrategy\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\n# Draft 2 - Technology & AI innovations\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-2.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-06\\nn: 2\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: evergreen\\nsource_date: 2026-07-06\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗱𝗿𝘂𝗱𝗴𝗲𝗿𝘆. 𝗕𝘂𝘁 𝘄𝗵𝗼'𝘀 𝘄𝗮𝘁𝗰𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗺?\\n\\nEvery company is now an \\\"AI company.\\\" Agents handling support, writing code, qualifying leads, running workflows.\\n\\nHere's what nobody talks about:\\n\\nAn AI agent is like hiring an intern who works 24/7, never complains, but also never tells you when they're about to make a catastrophic mistake.\\n\\nNo performance review. No guardrails. Just... output.\\n\\nThe companies that win with AI aren't the ones deploying the most agents. They're the ones who:\\n• Define clear boundaries for what agents CAN'T do\\n• Build observability so humans see when things go weird\\n• Test edge cases before customers find them\\n• Keep humans in the loop for high-stakes decisions\\n\\nAI doesn't replace judgment. It amplifies whatever you point it at — good or bad.\\n\\nWhat's the last thing you automated that maybe you shouldn't have?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #Automation #TechLeadership #FutureOfWork\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\n# Draft 3 - Personal development & mindset\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-3.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-06\\nn: 3\\npillar: Personal development & mindset\\nsource: evergreen\\nsource_date: 2026-07-06\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗴𝗮𝗽 𝗯𝗲𝘁𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗻 𝘄𝗵𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝘄𝗵𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝘄𝗮𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗯𝗲 𝗶𝘀 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗮 𝗹𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗼𝗳 𝗸𝗻𝗼𝘄𝗹𝗲𝗱𝗴𝗲.\\n\\nIt's a lack of reps.\\n\\nWe consume content, read books, take courses, follow thought leaders. We KNOW what to do. But knowing isn't doing.\\n\\nThe difference between the top 1% and everyone else isn't access to information — it's the willingness to be bad at something in public until you're not.\\n\\n• The writer who publishes daily even when nobody reads\\n• The founder who pitches 100 investors to get 1 yes\\n• The engineer who ships messy code and refactors later\\n\\nEvery expert was once a beginner who refused to quit.\\n\\nThe reps are free. The discomfort is the price.\\n\\nWhat are you putting off because you're \\\"not ready yet\\\"?\\n\\n#PersonalDevelopment #Growth #Mindset #Habits #Success\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\n# Mark brief as sent\\ntouch \\\"$PENDING_DIR/.brief-sent-$TODAY\\\"\\n\\necho \\\"DRAFTS_CREATED=3\\\"\\nls -la \\\"$PENDING_DIR/\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783298650850,"responseId":"XPpKaqSDJK3MwOYPubKOwA8"}}
