{"type":"message","id":"7aa94e01","parentId":"5a9c7c95","timestamp":"2026-07-06T00:44:54.059Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_148da81c788c4776ae446ef9","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 1/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗳𝗶𝗿𝘀𝘁 𝟭𝟬 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝘄𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗲 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗸𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴.\n\nThey'll come from conversations.\n\nThe startup myth: build it, launch it, run ads, scale. The reality? Most early customers come from direct outreach, founder-led sales, and word-of-mouth from people who actually know you.\n\nMarketing kicks in LATER — once you have signal on what resonates, who buys, and why they stay.\n\nBefore that? You're not a marketer. You're a salesperson with a prototype.\n\nThe founders who win early don't optimize funnels. They send 50 DMs a day, get on calls, listen to objections, and iterate. They build relationships with 10 people who become their first champions.\n\nThose 10 turn into 100. Then marketing scales it.\n\nBut you can't skip the unscalable part.\n\nWhat's one unscalable thing you're doing this week to get your next 10 customers?\n\n#Entrepreneurship #Startups #Sales #Growth #BusinessStrategy\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Evergreen (founder-led sales)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-06-1"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-06-1"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-06-1"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 1/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗳𝗶𝗿𝘀𝘁 𝟭𝟬 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝘄𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗲 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗸𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴.\\n\\nThey'll come from conversations.\\n\\nThe startup myth: build it, launch it, run ads, scale. The reality? Most early customers come from direct outreach, founder-led sales, and word-of-mouth from people who actually know you.\\n\\nMarketing kicks in LATER — once you have signal on what resonates, who buys, and why they stay.\\n\\nBefore that? You're not a marketer. You're a salesperson with a prototype.\\n\\nThe founders who win early don't optimize funnels. They send 50 DMs a day, get on calls, listen to objections, and iterate. They build relationships with 10 people who become their first champions.\\n\\nThose 10 turn into 100. Then marketing scales it.\\n\\nBut you can't skip the unscalable part.\\n\\nWhat's one unscalable thing you're doing this week to get your next 10 customers?\\n\\n#Entrepreneurship #Startups #Sales #Growth #BusinessStrategy\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Evergreen (founder-led sales)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-06-1\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-06-1\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-06-1\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783298683368,"responseId":"fPpKauXENOvJwOYPguHb-A8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5023d5d5-bc45-4945-a638-3cc45a164937","parentId":"7aa94e01","timestamp":"2026-07-06T00:44:54.346Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📝 Post 1/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗳𝗶𝗿𝘀𝘁 𝟭𝟬 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝘄𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗲 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗸𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴.\n\nThey'll come from conversations.\n\nThe startup myth: build it, launch it, run ads, scale. The reality? Most early customers come from direct outreach, founder-led sales, and word-of-mouth from people who actually know you.\n\nMarketing kicks in LATER — once you have signal on what resonates, who buys, and why they stay.\n\nBefore that? You're not a marketer. You're a salesperson with a prototype.\n\nThe founders who win early don't optimize funnels. They send 50 DMs a day, get on calls, listen to objections, and iterate. They build relationships with 10 people who become their first champions.\n\nThose 10 turn into 100. Then marketing scales it.\n\nBut you can't skip the unscalable part.\n\nWhat's one unscalable thing you're doing this week to get your next 10 customers?\n\n#Entrepreneurship #Startups #Sales #Growth #BusinessStrategy\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Evergreen (founder-led sales)"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1783298694330,"idempotencyKey":"5a1350eb-3b7b-4c98-8549-1099fe022d4f:message-tool:cnHkthG7TUuHvPWstyqEdE-c:call_148da81c788c4776ae446ef9"}}
